Package com.esri.mo2.cs.geom

Fundamental classes used for geometry calculations.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
ClementiniGeometry The methods in this interface implement the CBM (calculus-based methods) of Clementini et als.
Curve This interface implements an abstract class that represents simple linear objects, such as, arcs, segments, paths, and rings.
DisplayTransform This interface implements a transform from a Euclidean coordinate system (Y values increase upwards) to a Windows coordinate system (Y values increase downwards).
FeatureGeometry This interface implements a Geometry that can be stored externally.
Geometry This is the public interface for 2D ESRI geometry objects.
GeometryCollection This interface implements a homogenous collection of similar Geometries.
HitTest This interface implements a method to allow selection of a vertex within a MultiPoint, Polygon, or Polyline feature.
MPointCollection Adds Measures support to the point collection interface.
MultiPoint Implements a collection of Points.
MZPointCollection This interface adds support of M and Z to the point collection interface.
Path Implements a Path that consists of one or more points that represent a collection of straight-line segments.
PointApplicator Applies mass changes to the points in a feature geometry.
PointApplicatorUser Allows you to apply mass changes to the points in a feature geometry by using a PointApplicator.
PointCollection A prototypical collection of Points that exist in all Geometry classes and interfaces.
PointIterator Provides fast iterator support for point collections.
Polygon Implements a collection of one or more Rings.
Polyline Implements a collection of one or more paths.
Ring Implements a closed Path that forms a simple area object.
Segment Implements a Segment that defines a linear shape connecting two points.
SegmentCollection Implements a collection of straight-line Segments.
SegmentHitTest Defines a method to allow selection of a segment within a Polygon or Polyline.
Transform A transformation similar to java.awt.geom.AffineTransform, but is restricted to a common scale for both X and Y directions.
 

Class Summary
BaseDisplayTransform This class is the standard implementation of the Transform interface
BaseFeatureGeometry This class is the base implementation for FeatureGeometry.
BaseGeometry This class is the base implementation of Geometry.
BaseGeometry.GeometryComparator A comparison class which uses the geometries' envelope as a basis for comparison.
BaseGeometryArray Provides a simple array-based implementation of GeometryCollection.
BaseGeometryIterator A common utility used by the various PathIterator classes.
BaseLineSegments This implementation is intended for straight line segments only.
BaseMultiPoint This is a standard implementation of MultiPoint.
BaseMultiPointIterator Implements a path iterator suitable for delivering the points of a MultiPoint one at a time.
BasePath Standard implementation of Path.
BasePointIterator A Path iterator capable of delivering a Point to the esri Symbols.
BasePointsArray A standard Points implementation that stores one or more points within a pair of coordinate arrays - one array for X ordinates and the other for Y ordinates.
BasePointsArrayIterator Provides iterator support for BasePointArrays.
BasePolygon This class implements a polygon object.
BasePolygonIterator This class implements a PathIterator for Polygons.
BasePolyline An implementation of Polyline, appropriate for a fixed number of Paths.
BasePolylineIterator The PathIterator for Polylines.
BaseRing This class is an implementation of Ring.
BaseRingIterator This class implements a PathIterator for Rings.
BaseTransform This is the standard implementation of the Transform interface.
Clementini This class implements methods for the Clementini Geometry objects.
Cogo Provides frequently used CoOrdinate GeOmetry (COGO) methods and variables.
Envelope This class implements a 2D rectangular shape in world coordinates, used frequently for bitmap and selection purposes.
FeaturePoint This class implements a Point inside a feature.
Global  
HitResult This class contains information about the return of a HitTest.
Line This class implements a straight line connecting 2 Points.
MBasePointsArray A standard implementation of Points, that stores Point(s) within a pair of coordinate arrays, and a measured value array.
MBasePointsArrayIterator This class provides iterator support for MBasePointArrays.
MZBasePointsArray A standard implementation of Points that stores Point(s) within a pair of coordinate arrays, a measured value array, and a Z array.
MZBasePointsArrayIterator This class provides iterator support for MZBasePointArrays.
Point This class represents the Point type.
PointM This class represents a 2D Point with an additional measure value.
PointZ This class represents a 3D Point with an additional m or measure value.
RelativeCompare This class performs floating point comparisons between two numbers with relative precision (not absolute).
SegmentHitResult This class contains information about the return of a SegmentHitTest.
UnitVector2D This class implements a unit vector with an X component and Y component.
Vector2D This class implements a vector with a X component and Y component.
 

Exception Summary
BufferException Thrown by com.esri.mo2.cs.geom.FeatureGeometry.buffer() when a valid buffer cannot be created.
EmptyGeometryException Thrown by various geometry toAXL/fromAXL methods whenever conversion to/from AXL would result in an empty geometry.
GeometryException A generic Exception thrown by com.esri.mo2.cs.geom package methods.
InvalidDistanceException Thrown if the buffer distance is less than or equal to 0.0.
InvalidValuesException Thrown by com.esri.mo2.cs.geom.Global.parseEnvelope(), if the number of tokens in the given string is not equal to 4.
NotImplementedException Thrown by those methods that are not currently implemented.
